    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because compression-bending is the governing failure mode and the project requirements — documented in the credibility assessment narrative — establish that a single-configuration validation is sufficient for this device class and risk level. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support regulatory submission.",
